1. Recursive DFS: T.C. - O(N), S.C. - O(N)

Approach: If we have reached null for both trees, return true. And if the two nodes of 
different trees are equal then check for their children and when there children (both left
and right) then return true.

class Solution:
    def isSameTree(self, p: Optional[TreeNode], q: Optional[TreeNode]) -> bool:
        if not p and not q:
            return True
        if p and q and p.val == q.val:
            return self.isSameTree(p.left,q.left) and self.isSameTree(p.right,q.right)
        else:
            return False
